    "Management": {
      "text": "",
      "subsections": {
        "General_Fracture_Management": {
          "text": "Acute pain management\nOpen fractures\nrequire immediate IV antibiotics and urgent surgical washout\nNeurovascular compromise from fracture requires emergent reduction and/or orthopedic intervention\nConsider risk for\ncompartment syndrome",
          "tables": []
        },
        "Specific_Management": {
          "text": "Pain control in ED with\nfemoral nerve block\nNerve Block: Fascia Iliaca Compartment\n3 in 1 block (femoral, obturator, lateral cutaneous nerve of thigh)\nNo difference in 2 blocks listed above, which both reduced pain scores in the ED.\n[2]\nType and cross/screen for patients at higher risk of hemorrhage:\nAge > 75 yrs\nInitial hemoglobin < 12\nPeritrochanteric fracture",
          "tables": []
        }
      },
